      Classes in org.neo4j.bolt.v3.runtime that implement BoltStateMachineState 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      class  AbstractStreamingState
      When STREAMING, a result is available as a stream of records.
      class  ConnectedState
      Following the socket connection and a small handshake exchange to establish protocol version, the machine begins in the CONNECTED state.
      class  FailedState
      The FAILED state occurs when a recoverable error is encountered.
      class  FailSafeBoltStateMachineState  
      class  InterruptedState
      If the state machine has been INTERRUPTED then a RESET message has entered the queue and is waiting to be processed.
      class  ReadyState
      The READY state indicates that the connection is ready to accept a new RUN request.
      class  StreamingState
      When STREAMING, additionally attach bookmark to PULL_ALL, DISCARD_ALL result
      class  TransactionReadyState  
      class  TransactionStreamingState
